<TITLE> Tarique slips, hurts head in hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)Tarique Rahman slipped and injured himself in the prison ward bathroom at BSMMU Hospital Monday afternoon, doctors and a prisons official said. Inspector general of prisons, Brig Gen Zakir Hasan told bdnews24.com: "Tarique Rahman fell and sustained slight injuries to his back and forehead. His forehead has a slight cut." The top prison official said Tarique was expected to undergo a CT scan. Two of his doctors told bdnews24.com that the detained elder son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia was taking rest after being examined and treated. "Slipping on the floor of the bathroom, Tarique hit his head. There is some swelling but the injury is not serious," said his doctor, Prof MA Awal of the department of orthopaedics. Kazi Mazharul Islam Dolon, joint replacement specialist, said: "Tarique Rahman fell against a basin and hit the right side of his head, above his ear, and also hurt his hip, knee and ankle." Tarique was transferred to Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Medical University Hospital from Dhaka Central Jail, after his arrest on March 7, 2007. bdnews24.
